files.Summary:

files.Summary:

files.Summary:

Used to negotiate WebSocket extensions during the handshake, allowing for additional features and capabilities.

files.Summary:

files.Summary:

files.Summary:

files.Summary:

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.ProxyConnection
files.Summary:

Used to control whether the network connection to the proxy server should be kept open after the current transaction.

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.ProxyAuthorization
files.Summary:

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.Pragma
files.Summary:

files.Summary:

The HTTP Sec-GPC request header is part of the Global Privacy Control (GPC) mechanism to indicate whether the user consents to a website or service selling or sharing their personal information with third parties.

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.Dnt
files.Summary:

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.P3P
files.Summary:

files.Summary:

files.Summary:

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.AcceptEncoding

The HTTP Accept-Encoding header.

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.AcceptCharset
files.Summary:

files.Title: Sisk.Core.Http.HttpKnownHeaderNames.Accept
